  "prompt": "How do I start a startup if I have an idea ?",
  "response": "Here are key steps to start a startup:\n\n1. Validate Your Idea\n- Research market need\n- Talk to potential customers\n- Confirm there's real demand\n- Assess competition\n\n2. Develop a Business Plan\n- Define target market\n- Create business model\n- Outline revenue strategy\n- Set clear goals\n\n3. Build a Prototype/Minimum Viable Product (MVP)\n- Create initial version\n- Test core functionality\n- Get user feedback\n- Iterate and improve\n\n4. Funding Options\n- Personal savings\n- Friends and family\n- Angel investors\n- Venture capital\n- Crowdfunding\n- Startup grants\n\n5. Legal Considerations\n- Choose business structure\n- Register your company\n- Protect intellectual property\n- Obtain necessary licenses\n\n6. Build Your Team\n- Recruit complementary skills\n- Find co-founders\n- Hire initial employees\n- Create company culture\n\n7. Network and Connect\n- Attend startup events\n- Join entrepreneurial communities\n- Connect with mentors\n- Participate in startup accelerators\n\n8. Technical Development\n- Develop full product\n- Create scalable infrastructure\n- Focus on user experience\n- Plan technology stack\n\n9. Marketing and Growth\n- Build online presence\n- Use social media\n- Create marketing strategy\n- Acquire initial customers\n\n10. Continuous Learning and Adaptation",
